            <title>[BOOKKEEPER-23] Timeout requests</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/BOOKKEEPER-23</link>
                <project id="12311293" key="BOOKKEEPER">Bookkeeper</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If a client remains connected to a bookie, requests do not timeout. This is an undesirable behavior if a bookie is up but not responding to a request for some reason, like it is slow or has not handled an exception appropriately and did not respond to the client. I propose to add a timeout mechanism.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
