&lt;p&gt;Review request for bookkeeper.&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Summary&lt;br/&gt;
-------&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If a client remains connected to a bookie, requests do not timeout. This is an undesirable behavior if a bookie is up but not responding to a request for some reason, like it is slow or has not handled an exception appropriately and did not respond to the client. I propose to add a timeout mechanism.&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;This addresses bug &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/BOOKKEEPER-23&quot; title=&quot;Timeout requests&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;BOOKKEEPER-23&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;BOOKKEEPER-23&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br/&gt;
